          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Introduce TN_EVENT_RMA_SKIP event",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Introduce TN_EVENT_RMA_SKIP event\n\nTN_EVENT_RMA_SKIP is a target LND event used to signify that an RMA\noperation to push/pull the LNet payload should be skipped.\nTN_EVENT_RMA_SKIP is used when the LND operation is a bulk put or get\nand LNet has passed a mlength of zero or a NULL LNet message\ndescriptor to the LND. When TN_EVENT_RMA_SKIP is seen, the target LND\nwill immediately send a tagged messaged to the LND initiator\ncompleting the bulk operation.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9948\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ia243d596cfe1960a29a23001f1379696bd9b3430\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
